{
  "$comment": [
    "Golden Beans event-destination-router · Story 3.1 — the SHARED lifecycle fixtures.",
    "Sprint 3 QA requires identical fixtures running in BOTH repos' suites. This file is the",
    "canonical copy; the golden-beans copy must be byte-identical, which is checkable with",
    "`shasum -a 256` on both. Plain JSON, not TypeScript, precisely so that check is trivial",
    "and so neither repo's tsconfig or import conventions can make the two drift.",
    "",
    "Every envelope here is shaped exactly as golden-beans' buildEventEnvelope emits it:",
    "null/absent fields OMITTED (never sent as null), empty metadata/tags objects dropped",
    "entirely, and actor/subject present only when at least one half is — sometimes only one.",
    "The `minimal` and `partial` cases exist because that shaping is easy to code against",
    "wrongly and impossible to notice until a real delivery arrives.",
    "",
    "SPRINT 3 (founding-merchant-activation-ops) extended `lifecycle` from 6 to 14 entries",
    "-- the 8 new `merchant.<stage>` types README D2 adds. golden-beans' copy of this file",
    "and its pinned digest need the SAME update in the same change, or the identical-",
    "fixtures contract silently stops being true. See that repo's",
    "Roadmap/01-growth-engine/event-destination-router/miyagi-lifecycle-contract.md."
  ],

